        }
      },
      "Microstructure_Info": {
        "Microstructure_Text": {
          "original": "Fine equiaxed grains and coarse columnar grains. Average sizes of fine equiaxed grains were 1.49 μm for the AF sample, while coarse columnar grains were 1.84 μm. Cu-rich and Sc-rich precipitates along the equiaxed grain boundaries... TKD identified Al2Cu and AlCuSc phases. Average size of these precipitates to be 116±42 nm. Smaller precipitates within coarse grains (42±13 nm).",
          "simplified": "Bimodal grain structure (equiaxed ~1.49 μm, columnar ~1.84 μm). Al2Cu and AlCuSc precipitates at boundaries (~116 nm) and grain interiors (~42 nm)."
